    "title_en": "Bounds on axion-like particles from fully merged photons at the LHC",
    "abstract_en": "I show that, in the mass range $0.1\\,\\text{GeV} < m_a < 6\\,\\text{GeV}$, the strongest current bound on axion-like particles (ALPs) coupled to photons comes from very high energy $aγ$ production at the LHC. In this regime, the two photons from the ALP decay are collimated and reconstructed as a single photon.",
